decision_conditions:
The development hereby permitted shall be begun no later than the  expiration of three years from the date of this permission.

Reason: In order to comply with the requirements of Section 91 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990.
description: Variation of condition 2 of approved permission 2181/18: Reduction of ground floor footprint; alterations to internal layout, elevations, roof tiles; installation of timber cladding and use of render, and installation of aluminium fenestrations (Summary)
